$ Bash built-in: set -x (set -o xtrace)
@ set

`set -x` (long notation: `set -o xtrace`) traces commands before executing them.

The value of the `PS4` variable is expanded and printed before the actual debug output.
-
In the following example, PS4 uses `$(date …)` to include the actual value of the hour, minute and second. It also uses
→ Linux/shell/ANSI-escape-sequences[ANSI escape sequences] to distinguish between script output and debug output.

{ run.sh

  gh|about-Bash|/built-in/set/x/run.sh||

}
{ script-1.sh

  gh|about-Bash|/built-in/set/x/script-1.sh||

}
{ script-2.sh

  gh|about-Bash|/built-in/set/x/script-2.sh||

}
{ script-3.sh

  gh|about-Bash|/built-in/set/x/script-3.sh||

}

